<taxonomicNameLabel box="[914,1004,727,753]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
on the basis of male terminalia, but is distinguished from the latter by a broader cercus and postgonite and shorter apical section of the phallus (
<figureCitation box="[1331,1416,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 66–70" captionStartId="66.[151,264,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,249,1802]" captionTargetId="figure-45@66.[151,1436,237,1836]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURES 66–70. Male terminalia of Iteaphila with unbranched R. 66, I. oedalina (Zetterstedt), posterior view; 67, same, 4+5 lateral view; 68, I. polygyna (Melander), lateral view; 69, I. recurvata sp. nov., lateral view; 70, I. sakhalinensis sp. nov., lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: pgt—postgonite; ph—phallus; sur—surstylus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745618" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4745618/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
